Satellite Sites:

*Available services: Public Peering, Private VLAN, Multicast streams, Virtual Patch.*

data.name: IX Liverpool
data.notes:
IX Liverpool is a local internet exchange point located within the cultural city of Liverpool within the United Kingdom. We are a collaborative, co-operative and mutual organisation, founded as a not-for-profit company and funded by our members and voluntary contributions from our local community.

We have an open joining policy for members and welcome competitive networks large and small to join and enjoy not only the local connectivity options at the exchange but to make use of the business networking opportunities, the range of public talks we put on throughout the year and the various peering workshops for members that we organise.
